@startuml
title Docs frontend — Command palette state machine

' Single-page palette opened from any docs page via the global hotkey.
' Closed and Open are the steady states; everything else is in-flight.

[*] --> Closed

Closed   : palette overlay hidden\nbody scroll unlocked\nfocus on the page
Open     : palette overlay visible\nempty input, full result list\nfocus inside palette
Filtering: input has at least one character\nresult list filtered live\nfirst result auto-highlighted
Selected : a result row is highlighted\nactivation runs that row's command
Closing  : closing animation in flight\nfocus restoration scheduled

Closed    --> Open      : Cmd / Ctrl + K\n— or — toolbar trigger
Open      --> Filtering : input changes (length > 0)
Filtering --> Open      : input cleared (length = 0)
Open      --> Selected  : ArrowDown / Up / hover
Filtering --> Selected  : ArrowDown / Up / hover
Selected  --> Selected  : ArrowDown / Up
Selected  --> Open      : input cleared
Selected  --> Closing   : Enter\n(execute selected row)
Open      --> Closing   : Escape\nclick on backdrop
Filtering --> Closing   : Escape\nclick on backdrop
Selected  --> Closing   : Escape
Closing   --> Closed    : transition end\nfocus restored

note right of Open
  result rows are virtualized for >200 entries
  data source: docs-portal-data.js
end note

note right of Selected
  row activation may be:
  - navigate to URL
  - copy to clipboard
  - run a registered command
end note

@enduml
